const wchar_t szHelp[]=L"vear v1.0\r\nSite: https://github.com/Yuri213212/vear\r\nCopyright (C) 2016-2020 Yuri213212\r\nEmail: yuri213212@vip.qq.com\r\nLicense: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0\r\nhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\r\n\r\nThis program monitors and analyzes recording device in real-time.\r\n\r\nThe screen is split into 2 parts.\r\nThe top is wave view and the bottom is spectrum view.\r\nThe bar at bottom is an image of the top of piano keybord.\r\nThe place with little red square is absolute C-4 by default.\r\nThe y-axis of spectrum view is logarithmic,\r\nranged from -48dB to 0dB by default.\r\n\r\nUse vertical scroll bar or up/down arrow key to change gain.\r\nPress alphabetic key to change transpose.\r\nHorizontal scroll bar and left/right arrow key can also change transpose.\r\nPress 'Mode' button or tab key to toggle source of spectrum view.\r\nSource can be the output of virtual neural network or raw data.\r\nPress 'Color' button to change color of spectrum view.\r\nPress 'Pause' button or space key to pause/resume analyzing.\r\nPress 'Reset' button or Esc key to reset program state.";
